function minStonesRemaining(piles, k) {
    for (let i = 0; i < k; i++) {
        let max_pile_index = 0;
        for (let j = 1; j < piles.length; j++) {
            if (piles[j] > piles[max_pile_index]) {
                max_pile_index = j;
            }
        }
        piles[max_pile_index] -= Math.floor(piles[max_pile_index] / 2);
    }

    return piles.reduce((total, pile) => total + pile, 0);
}
```


    The algorithm follows these steps:
1. Iterate `k` times.
2. For each iteration, find the index of the largest pile.
3. Reduce the largest pile by half, rounding down, and update the value in the piles array.
4. After all iterations, compute the sum of the remaining piles and return it.

